The paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks for analyzing very high resolution satellite imagery for land-use, urban density, and population distribution maps. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) categories. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for feature representation and classification, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of geospatial data for analysis, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category.
